The Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee held a meeting on Thursday to study and analyze current economic circumstances and make plans for related work in the second half of 2022. The meeting was chaired by Xi Jinping, general secretary of the CPC Central Committee. Since the beginning of this year, China has effectively coordinated COVID-19 prevention and control with economic and social development, it was noted at the meeting. To ensure sound economic work for the second half of 2022, the importance of upholding the underlying principle of pursuing progress while ensuring stability was stressed at the meeting, alongside the full, accurate and comprehensive implementation of the new development philosophy, as well as accelerating efforts to create a new development pattern and promote high-quality development.